nd}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}, {\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}) is bivariate normal, then CoVaR based on {\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend} = VaR{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}({\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}) is not an increasing function of the correlation parameter. Similar issues arise in the bivariate {\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend} model and in the model with {\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend} margins and a Gumbel copula. In all these cases, CoVaR based on {\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend} {$\geq$} VaR{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}({\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}{\dbend}) is an increasing function of the dependence parameter.},
